APPENDIX.

IMITATIONS OF THEOCRITUS.

[The whole form and diction of the Eclogues is largely inspired by Theocritus, and the small points of imitation are immensely numerous. It is only proposed here to select the principal points, where a whole phrase or idea is taken from the Greek.]
